# @mcp-stack/core

## Role
Shared infrastructure used by ALL MCP servers. Changes here affect every service.
Be extra careful — build and test before committing.

## Modules

| Module | Lines | Deps | Purpose |
|--------|-------|------|---------|
| `logger.ts` | 190 | zero | Structured JSON on stderr. Levels, child loggers, request ID, secret redaction |
| `oauth.ts` | 435 | Express types | OAuth 2.1 DCR+PKCE: SessionStore, PendingCodeStore, ClientRegistry, bearer middleware |
| `cache.ts` | 76 | zero | In-memory TTL cache with prefix invalidation |
| `tool-helpers.ts` | 136 | MCP SDK | `createToolRegistrar()` — one-liner tool registration with error handling + timing |
| `audit-logger.ts` | 188 | zero | Write-action audit trail. Buffers locally, flushes via pluggable upload fn |

## Guidelines
- Zero external runtime deps where possible (logger, cache, audit)
- Every new utility must have Vitest tests
- Export everything through `index.ts`
- Don't add service-specific logic here — this is infrastructure only
- If a utility is only used by one service, it belongs in that service's package

## Testing
47 tests across logger, cache, oauth suites:
```bash
npm test
npx vitest run --reporter=verbose
```
All tests must pass before any commit to core.

## Logger Usage
```typescript
import { createLogger } from '@mcp-stack/core'
const logger = createLogger('service-name')
logger.info('message', { key: 'value' })
logger.child({ requestId: '...' }).debug('scoped log')
```
Secret redaction: any value matching token/password/secret/key patterns is auto-redacted in logs.
